	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=157066"><span id=" ">Aeoniq</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">18 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>I have completed this quest. I wear the pitted Iron Ring.&nbsp;&nbsp;Granted we are killing things that  are  near in  value or greater for the ring slot, I chose to do this quest a long  time ago, before PoP and Luclin. <br/><br/>Such  comparable rings are the Innovator's ring from Xanamech, Ring of Lightning from Tormax, Wing Ring from Dromok , ect.  These are all  equally if not geater rings, with much less effort involved.<br/>However as I has stated, I had already invested  much time into this quest and i was going to  finish it. Thats just the way i am. If i set my  sights on something  , eventually i well get it,  as i do everything i can  to make  sure that  happens.<br/><br/>Some things to Note about this quest...<br/>AT all times it seems you need MAX ally CoV faction.  I Used to carry the &quot;vial of kromzek blood&quot; on my  person, so  the next time my guild caught , Klandicar, Sontalak, Zlandicar, ect., i would be ready.<br/>So  I caught Klandicar up and we kiled him. No biggy, till i  had everyone zone into DN and i  said the phrases to get ready to spawn Garzicor.<br/>Fooker ate my blood, and said &quot;I will do nothing  for the likes  of you&quot;,  I was kindly from the  klandicar kill and thought little of  that  issue before hand.<br/><br/>So i redid the quest again. from step 1,  except i still had my &quot;Assembled Naginata&quot;,  I did have to make everything  fin order to recieve that  &quot;vial of kromzek blood&quot; again. I  caught Klandicar up again and we killed  him, except this time i zoned into DN when  kland was at 20% to  save myself from  the faction hit.<br/><br/>Anyways, still buffed and  ready  i had the guildies  play  with this dragon. The first one has the Dragon Construct model and has  abit more hit points than a normal  construct. I can solo those. This &quot;Garzicor's Corpse&quot; hit near 200's and had no special attacks, I'd guesstimate  100k+ hp,  or so.  The  second  dragon, ( Phara Dar model) Hit  high 300's, seemed to  triple or quad. Roughly 200k - 250k Hp.  Had an AE slow  with  some DD damage, although i didnt note how much the DD  was at the time..  It wasnt like &quot;Silver breath&quot; like the  unresistable 400 dd from Kland, Doze, ect.  It seemed like  200ish  or less,  maybe i was   resisting it partially , i dunno. Like i said, i wasnt paying attention  to the AE damage since  at the time it seemed rather minor.<br/><br/>Took us 3-4 mins or so  to kill  the final dragon, but then again  i dont think anybody had GoD buff on at the time. I didnt think it had a &quot;Dragon fear&quot; AE as well, so  1/2 the raid was  running in fear for a good  bit lol. <br/>WOuld say this encounter is roughly Klandicar level,  maybe easier,   just wasnt prepared for the AE fear.<br/><br/>I  personally like the quest alot, i rated it well.  For an  older quest the reward is  still nice. Also i  dont have to spend DKP  on a ring or  equal or near value and  save my points for  something  better suited for a different slot. All in all , this quest is  difficult  somewhat,  but  worth it , i think, if you stick it out. Then again, this quest is not for everybody. I would rather quest an item than   loot it off some uberkill_09, but thats just me. <br/><br/><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=266327 target=akztarg> Magelo </a><br/><br/></p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br /><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=266327 target=akztarg>Roinin Unsleep</a><br/>70th Master Elementalist -Rodcet Nife<br/></td></tr>
